You have any you want to share?

00:22:13.055 --> 00:22:15.040
CHRIS BUTSCH: Let's see.

00:22:15.040 --> 00:22:17.030
Oh, there was this
time in Cozumel.

00:22:17.030 --> 00:22:18.790
I love talking to cabbies.

00:22:18.790 --> 00:22:21.290
Cabbies, rickshaw
drivers generally--

00:22:21.290 --> 00:22:26.370
they're sort of undercover
sociologists and psychologists,

00:22:26.370 --> 00:22:29.400
because who else listens to
somebody else's life story

00:22:29.400 --> 00:22:31.483
every single day.

00:22:31.483 --> 00:22:33.150
These people have so
many conversations.

00:22:33.150 --> 00:22:35.280
They're generally
buckets of wisdom.

00:22:35.280 --> 00:22:37.320
And I love talking
to these guys.

00:22:37.320 --> 00:22:41.120
So we got in the cab in
Cozumel, and I said the usual.

00:22:41.120 --> 00:22:43.500
Hey, Miguel, I'm
studying happiness.

00:22:43.500 --> 00:22:46.200
I love asking people
what makes them happy.

00:22:46.200 --> 00:22:47.670
And he cuts me
off, and he goes, I

00:22:47.670 --> 00:22:49.462
will take you to where
they make happiness.

00:22:49.462 --> 00:22:53.724
[LAUGHTER]

00:22:53.724 --> 00:22:56.340
Well, what does that mean?

00:22:56.340 --> 00:22:58.390
And he doesn't ask
me where I'm going,

00:22:58.390 --> 00:23:02.850
or where I want to go, you
know, his job as a cab driver.

00:23:02.850 --> 00:23:06.060
Instead, he just drives me
to where they make happiness.

00:23:06.060 --> 00:23:07.370
So I'm in Cozumel.

00:23:07.370 --> 00:23:12.690
Does anyone have a guess where
they would make happiness?

00:23:12.690 --> 00:23:13.650
It begins with a "T."

00:23:13.650 --> 00:23:14.400
AUDIENCE: Tequila?

00:23:14.400 --> 00:23:15.150
CHRIS BUTSCH: Yes!

00:23:15.150 --> 00:23:16.232
It's a tequila farm.

00:23:16.232 --> 00:23:17.940
He drove me to his
cousin's tequila farm.

00:23:17.940 --> 00:23:19.980
[LAUGHTER]

00:23:19.980 --> 00:23:21.450
He pulls out this little--

00:23:21.450 --> 00:23:22.720
I watched the whole process.

00:23:22.720 --> 00:23:24.200
It's actually
pretty fascinating.

00:23:24.200 --> 00:23:26.040
And at the very
end of the process,

00:23:26.040 --> 00:23:28.040
tequila is dribbling down
the sugar chute that's

00:23:28.040 --> 00:23:30.230
capturing the perfect
amount of sugar,

00:23:30.230 --> 00:23:33.090
and it just drips into
this little Dixie cup.

00:23:33.090 --> 00:23:35.580
And he hands me the
Dixie cup, and he goes,

00:23:35.580 --> 00:23:37.800
my friend, your journey is over.

00:23:37.800 --> 00:23:40.890
[LAUGHTER]

